# Basic Linux Commands
cd --> Change Directory
pwd --> Prit Working Directory
ls --> List Contents of a Directory
cd .. --> Go back one directory
cd - --> Return to the previous directory
whoami --> Prints username
clear --> Clearing the screen
cp --> Copy
rm --> Remove
adduser --> Add user to the system
which --> shows the path of the file/used to determined the location of an executable file in the system.
apropos --> search the manual page descriptions for given a keyword.
sudo --> Super user
"sudo chmod +rx <directory>" --> Granting read and execute permissions for a directory.
